info.headline: High Wind Warning issued November 20 at 3:18AM PST until November 21 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Oxnard
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM PST TUESDAY... * WHAT...Areas of north to northeast 30 to 50 mph with gusts to 70 mph. Local gusts to 80 mph in the western San Gabriel mountains today. * WHERE...Southern Ventura County Mountains, Interstate 5 Corridor and Western San Gabriel Mountains and Highway 14 Corridor. * WHEN...Until 10 AM PST Tuesday. * IMPACTS...Damaging winds will blow down large objects such as trees and power lines. Power outages are likely. Travel will be difficult, especially for drivers of high profile vehicles.
info.instruction: People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around large trees. If possible, remain indoors and avoid windows. Use extra caution if you must drive.
